<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4046] 1 == new Object() throws ClassCastException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4046</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;Example 1:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;assertFalse(new Object() == 1) // this is ok&lt;br/&gt;
assertFalse(1 == new Object()) // this throws a ClassCastException, because Groovy redirects the call to java.lang.Integer.compareTo(Integer i)&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Example 2:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;enum MyEnum &lt;/p&gt;
{ A, B, C }

&lt;p&gt;assertFalse(new Object() == MyEnum.A) // this is ok&lt;br/&gt;
assertFalse(MyEnum.A == new Object()) // this throws a ClassCastException, because Groovy redirects the call to java.lang.Enum.compareTo(E e) where E extends java.lang.Enum&amp;lt;E&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>tested for 1.7.0 and 1.6.0</environment>
        <key id="12815075">GROOVY-4046</key>
